| -m || IP || This tells OpenTTD to start a multiplayer game. You use IP, ([http://www.whatismyip.com What is my ip?]) to connect to a server, where IP is replaced by the hosts IP (He must have started the game with -m first). If you want to test if it works and if you got it right, then you start a game with -m and a second game with -m 127.0.0.1, that will make you join you're own game (127.0.0.1 is localhost) || 
