| -p || Player ID || With this, you can make coop games, sort of, where multiple players control the same company. Replace "Player ID" with the number of the player. Start counting from the top of the player list. 

This is also useful for re-joining network games that you have become de-synchronised from for whatever reason. (some patience may be required to get a good reconnect) Just remember that in-game player numbers go from 1-8 and the commandline option is from 0-7 so subtract one from the in-game number.

